{"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Migrating to 1.9","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore"},{"text":" which gives a succinct syntax for sending actions with case key paths, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)"},{"text":" method for overriding dependencies.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.9"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Sending test store actions","level":3,"anchor":"Sending-test-store-actions"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.4 of the library introduced the ability to receive test store actions using case key path","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"syntax, massively simplifying how one asserts on actions received in a test:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["-store.receive(.child(.presented(.response(.success(\"Hello\")))))","+store.receive(\\.child.response.success)"],"syntax":"diff"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"While version 1.6 of the library introduced the ability to assert against the payload of a received","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"action:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["store.receive(\\.child.presented.success, \"Hello\")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.9 introduces similar affordances for "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sending"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" actions to test stores via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore\/send(_:_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". These methods can significantly simplify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integration-style tests that send deeply-nested actions to child features, and provide symmetry to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how actions are received:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .destination(.presented(.record(.startButtonTapped))))))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.startButtonTapped)"," store.receive(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.timerTick)"],"syntax":"diff"},{"type":"aside","style":"tip","name":"Tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Case key paths offer specialized syntax for many different action types.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction"},{"type":"text","text":"’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"presented"},{"type":"text","text":" case can be collapsed:"}]},{"code":["-store.send(.destination(.presented(.tap)))","+store.send(\\.destination.tap)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/IdentifiedAction","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" can be subscripted into:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .tap)))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].tap)"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"s can dynamically chain into a key path of state:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.binding(.set(\\.firstName, \"Blob\")))","+store.send(\\.binding.firstName, \"Blob\")"],"type":"codeListing"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Together, these helpers can massively simplify asserting against nested actions:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(","-  .path(","-    .element(","-      id: 0,","-      action: .destination(","-        .presented(","-          .sheet(","-            .binding(","-              .set(\\.password, \"blobisawesome\")","-            )","-          )","-        )","-      )","-    )","-  )","-)","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.sheet.binding.password, \"blobisawesome\")"]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Overriding dependencies","level":3,"anchor":"Overriding-dependencies"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.2 of "},{"identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" introduced an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"alternative syntax for referencing a dependency:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing","code":["-@Dependency(\\.apiClient) var apiClient","+@Dependency(APIClient.self) var apiClient"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The primary benefit of this syntax is that you do not need to define a dedicated computed property"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DependencyValues"},{"type":"text","text":", which saves a small amount of boilerplate."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is now a similar API for overriding dependencies on a reducer, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which can be used like so:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["MyFeature()","  .dependency(mockAPIClient)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type of "},{"code":"mockAPIClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" determines how the dependency is overridden."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This style of accessing and overriding dependencies is really only appropriate for dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"defined directly in your project. If you are shipping a dependency client that is used by others,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then still prefer adding a computed property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DependencyValues"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to be more discoverable."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/Composab